Josef Zygmunt Szulc (4 April 1875, Warsaw, Warsaw Governorate, Russian Empire – 10 April 1956, Paris, France) was a composer and conductor.

He also lived in Berlin briefly (using the name Joseph Schultz) and later moved to Paris to complete his studies in conducting and composition in 1899, converting the spelling of his first name to Joseph.
In 1903 he moved to Brussels, where he was made chief conductor at the Théâtre de la Monnaie and saw instant success with his ballet Ispahan and several tunes.
In 1907 he completed the music for Marcel Gerbidon's operetta, Flossie or Je m'appelle Flossie.
In 1908 he adapted Pierre Veber's comedy Loute, then in 1914 began the musical comedy Flup !
